{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"418a4103-8a1c-4e93-8e47-f6383c1f6c5c","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\n\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is a classic untestable static call. It's hard to mock because it's called directly inside the function body.\n\n### Why it's a problem\n- You can't control the time in tests, making time-dependent assertions flaky or impossible.\n- `datetime.now()` also returns a **naive** datetime (no timezone), which is discouraged in Django.\n\n### Recommended fix\nUse Django's `django.utils.timezone.now()` instead — it's timezone-aware **and** easily mockable with [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) or `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\n**Summary:** Only 1 file, 1 occurrence found. The project is small, so the fix is straightforward. Want me to apply it?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9eb9160f-bec9-4af5-852b-b37cb7d38633","outputTokens":261,"requestId":"BD11:21BACA:1C8FA0A:204B36B:6A07C5FF"},"id":"ac73fc81-7683-40fe-83a7-ee2cc2105a9c","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:19:04.249Z","parentId":"cce94e40-7b3c-4ee8-9204-ff2a55a872a8"}
